        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the UnstructuredDocument data structure — the intermediate output of document readers containing flat lines, tables, and attachments before structure extraction. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Raw document content: flat line list, tables, attachments, metadata, warnings. \par \b Input\/ \:  Tables, lines, attachments, optional warnings and metadata. \par \b Output\/ \:  UnstructuredDocument instance consumed by structure extractors. \par \b Links\/ \:  [READS_DATA_FROM(9): LineWithMeta, Table, AttachedFile] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>warnings is never None (defaults to empty list)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>metadata is never None (defaults to empty dict) \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why a separate &quot;unstructured&quot; phase? A: Readers output flat line lists with format-specific tags; structure extractors then assign hierarchy levels and build the document tree. This separation enables independent reader and extractor development. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 10[Unstructured document container] =&gt; UnstructuredDocument METHOD 5[Get full raw text] =&gt; get_text \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[UnstructuredDocument]: Reader → ReturnRawDocument → UnstructuredDocumentProduced</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>[UnstructuredDocument]: StructureExtractor → BuildDocumentTree → ParsedDocumentCreated </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
